data.enText: a level of a building; a floor

data.chText: 房子的上面 / 下面一层
data.enText: the upper/lower storey of the house
having the number of levels mentioned

data.chText: storey（英国英语）／story（北美英语）主要用以指建筑物的楼层数目：
data.enText: You use storey ( BrE ) / story ( NAmE ) mainly when you are talking about the number of levels a building has.
The office building is five storeys high.

data.chText: floor主要指居住或前往等的某楼层：
data.enText: Floor is used mainly to talk about which particular level in the building someone lives on, goes to, etc.
His office is on the fifth floor.

tr: a structure consisting of a room or set of rooms at a single position along a vertical scale
example: what level is the office on?

value.boxr_value: in AM, use 美国英语用 story

value.def: A storey of a building is one of its different levels, which is situated above or below other levels.

example.ex: Houses must not be more than two storeys high.
example.tran: 房子的高度不得超过两层。

example.ex: ...the upper storeys of the Empire State Building.
example.tran: 帝国大厦的最上面几层
